Someone said fireworks is broken, I don't understand how that's possible since there must be an e2e test checking it. This is what he has to say:

After updating to a build from April 14, all requests to Fireworks AI (kimi-k2p5-turbo) fail with 400 Bad Request. Same config worked fine on my April 9 build. Fireworks Fire Pass only supports this model, so the provider is completely unusable.

The root cause might be related to the new schema normalization introduced around April 13. I noticed the new pipeline strips "type" from enum properties:

// Working (old) 
"action": { "enum": ["navigate", "click"], "type": "string" }

// Broken (new) 
"action": { "enum": ["navigate", "click"] }

Same thing happens with booleans ({"type": "boolean"} → {"enum": [false, true]}) and nullable enum anyOf branches.

I tried to roll back to verify this theory, but Moltis was not able to read the old config file anymore.

